      {
        "block_label": "text",
        "block_content": "In this work, we introduce a novel membership inference attack method specifically designed for diffusion models. Our approach only requires access to the variation API of the model, bypassing the need for internal network components such as the U-net. This represents an advancement for commercial diffusion models, which typically restrict internal access. We demonstrate the effectiveness of our approach across various datasets, showing that it achieves high accuracy in identifying whether an image was included in the training dataset. Our algorithm can detect data misuse.",
        "block_bbox": [
          618,
          1217,
